text: Franklin County is a county in the U.S. state of Georgia. As of the 2020 census, 23,424 people lived there. The county seat is Carnesville. ==References== Category:18th-century establishments in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:1780s establishments in the United States Category:1784 establishments in the United States Category:Georgia (U.S. state) counties
